This paper deals with learning methods in differentiable games, which are a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The paper discusses algorithms for improving learning dynamics in these games, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses theoretical guarantees for these algorithms, which could place it under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses multi-agent reinforcement learning, which could place it under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) or multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
